# Windows batch installers MUST be CRLF in every working tree — including the
# Linux GitHub Actions runner that builds dist/ and deploys them to Pages. Git
# normalizes to LF in the repo; `eol=crlf` forces CRLF back on checkout on all
# platforms (core.autocrlf alone only does this on Windows checkouts, so a Linux
# CI deploy would otherwise ship LF-only .bat files, where multi-line if() blocks
# can misbehave in cmd.exe).
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf
